{
  "project_id": "00000000-0000-4000-8000-partypassport1",
  "version": 1,
  "description": "Ultra Super Party Passport — inference pipeline. A webhook receives a JSON job (leg + graph context as text), a single reasoning agent runs the leg (belief-cluster naming OR hidden_prompt + magic_inference generation), and the answer returns as JSON.",
  "isLocked": false,
  "snapToGrid": true,
  "snapGridSize": [
    10,
    10
  ],
  "docRevision": 1,
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "webhook_1",
      "provider": "webhook",
      "name": "Party Webhook",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "webhook",
        "name": "Party Webhook"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 50,
          "y": 200
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "question_1",
      "provider": "question",
      "name": "Job Normalizer",
      "config": {
        "type": "question",
        "name": "Job Normalizer"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 360,
          "y": 200
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "text",
          "from": "webhook_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_passport",
      "provider": "agent_deepagent",
      "name": "Passport Inference",
      "config": {
        "profile": "default",
        "default": {
          "advanced_mode": true,
          "agent_description": "Passport Inference — runs one inference leg per request for the Ultra Super Party Passport. Reads a JSON job, returns raw JSON. Writes nothing, delegates nothing.",
          "system_prompt": "You are the Passport Inference engine for Ultra Super Party Passport, a graph-backed app that helps people at a party find who to meet.\n\nYou receive ONE user message: a JSON object with a `leg` field that names the job. You answer directly — you NEVER call the `task` tool, you NEVER delegate, you write no files. Your entire reply is a single raw JSON object with no markdown fences, no commentary, no leading or trailing text.\n\n=== Input contract ===\n\nThe incoming JSON always has `leg`. Two legs exist.\n\n1. leg == \"cluster_name\"\n   Shape: { \"leg\": \"cluster_name\", \"beliefs\": [\"<belief text>\", \"<belief text>\", ...] }\n   These belief statements were grouped (by embedding similarity, upstream) because they express one shared value. Name that value.\n   You MUST reply with exactly: { \"name\": \"<2-4 word value name, Title Case>\", \"basis\": \"<one sentence naming the shared value these beliefs express>\" }\n   The `name` is a human-facing cluster label (e.g. \"Radical Honesty\", \"Build In Public\", \"Slow Craft\"). The `basis` is one plain sentence a person could nod at.\n\n2. leg == \"passport_inference\"\n   Shape: { \"leg\": \"passport_inference\", \"person\": { \"name\": \"...\", \"line2\": \"...\", \"activities\": [\"...\"], \"beliefs\": [\"...\"], \"school\": \"...\", \"major\": \"...\" }, \"match\": { \"name\": \"...\", \"shared\": \"<what the graph says they share>\", \"path_summary\": \"<the real graph path connecting them, e.g. both DOES improv; both BELIEVES in-cluster Radical Honesty>\" } }\n   `person` is the passport holder. `match` is one person the graph already chose for them, with the real connecting path. Do not invent facts beyond what is given — ground every word in `shared` and `path_summary`.\n   You MUST reply with exactly: { \"hidden_prompt\": \"<a warm, specific, first-person opener the holder could say to walk up to match.name, grounded in the shared path; 1-2 sentences; no placeholders>\", \"magic_inference\": \"<one non-obvious, delightful sentence connecting the two people that goes one hop beyond the stated path>\" }\n\n=== Hard rules ===\n\n- Output raw JSON only. First character is `{`, last character is `}`.\n- Use ONLY the fields the leg specifies. No extra keys.\n- If a field you need is missing from the input, still return valid JSON for that leg, degrading gracefully (say the value plainly) rather than erroring or emitting prose.\n- If `leg` is missing or unrecognized, reply: { \"error\": \"unknown_leg\" }\n- Never mention that you are an AI, never describe your reasoning, never wrap the JSON in backticks.",
          "name": "Passport Inference"
        },
        "name": "Passport Inference"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 700,
          "y": 200
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "question_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_anthropic_passport",
      "provider": "llm_anthropic",
      "name": "Anthropic Passport",
      "config": {
        "profile": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "claude-sonnet-4-6": {
          "modelSource": "manual",
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_ANTHROPIC_KEY}"
        },
        "name": "Anthropic Passport"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 700,
          "y": 360
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent_passport"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "response_answers_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "name": "Return Answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers",
        "name": "Return Answers"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 1020,
          "y": 200
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent_passport"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
